The paper deals with algorithms for solving connectivity problems on graphs parameterized by treedepth, which is a fundamental graph parameter studied in the field of graph algorithms and data structures. The paper also mentions dynamic programming algorithms on tree decompositions, which is a common technique used in the subfield of dynamic programming and graph algorithms. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also uses the Cut\&Count technique, which is a popular technique in the subfield of parameterized complexity (cs.CC). The problems studied in the paper, such as Connected Vertex Cover, Feedback Vertex Set, Steiner Tree, Connected Dominating Set, and Connected Odd Cycle Transversal, are all related to graph theory (cs.CG) and graph algorithms (cs.GT).
